pan><hr size=1> ...and if he's on a masked IP, please ban that entire domain.<br><br>He's enjoying the loss of lives, and making jokes about it. &nbsp;I'm sure everyone else will agree that enjoyment of this situation <b>does not</b> belong here. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uraedwulf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raedwulf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 258<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/12/01 8:48:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=140.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ogmuk, please ban Mors...</span><hr size=1> Kanibaal:  Mors doesn't have an opinion.  He's just a sick and twisted little piece of garbage that is saying vile things because he can.  He isn't stating an opinion that must be protected, but trying to get kicks at someone elses expense.<br><br>Let's ban him.  Then, let's track him down and tell his parents, his teachers, his friends and everyone else around this pathetic waste of oxygen what he's said and done.  That'll be quite appropriate. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uraedwulf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raedwulf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 261<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/12/01 9:45:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=140.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ogmuk, please ban Mors...</span><hr size=1> I agree with you regarding the &quot;Nuke them all . . .&quot; camp.  See my post in the &quot;Racism Conference&quot; thread.  However, Mors is not stating an opinion, so does not need protection.  He's not making a political, social or religious statement, he's doing the equivalent of shouting &quot;Fire&quot; in a crowded theater.  That kind of crap isn't protected.  The persons doing so should be punished. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uiceweaselx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ice Weasel X</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 153<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/12/01 9:58:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=140.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ogmuk, please ban Mors...</span><hr size=1> <blockquote><i>Taken directly from Ogmuk's <b><a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrmessageboardrules.showMessage?topicID=2.topic">Rules of the Erollisi Marr EzBoard</a></b></i><hr>5) Anything deemed sexually or racially discriminating, or of an equally offensive nature will be deleted and the administrator and moderators may choose to ban the author (depends on the post).<br>...<br>7) The administrator and moderators are allowed to delete and modify posts/threads and/or ban you without giving you, or anyone else, an explanation.<br>...<br>14) If you post in the forums <a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes">Rants and Flames</a> or <a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrscammeralert">Scammer Alert</a>, you have to sign the posts with your in-game character name (read rule #3 for more information!). If your ezboard account is named after it, this is not necessary of course. For your info, the name of your level 3 twink camped in Freeport will not suffice, if you flame someone and this other person doesn’t know who you are and requests for a deletion of the post, it’ll be considered an anonymous flame and therefore will be deleted. And as always, when you continue the idiocy, you'll get banned (read “banishment”).<br>...<br>Banishment<br><br>Since you can swap from ISP (and thus IP address) in an eyewink we have added a few rules.<br><br>1) The administrator and moderators are allowed to do everything to get you banned from this board. Not only may they ban your IP, but they are also allowed to publicize your IP address (and all the other information you provided us with when you became a registered member on this board) that allows people to write complains to your ISP (Internet Service Provider).<br><br>2) The administrator and moderators are allowed to write all your information (IP address, other EzBoard accounts, the guild you’re in) on the board so other people can prevent that you will be ruining their board also.<hr></blockquote>Judging by the vast majority of posts on the attacks, I don't think I'm off base by saying Mors is posting material that is <i>at least</i> as offensive as a sexual or racial attack. &nbsp;Even some of the most heated enemies on these boards have (for the time being) put their differences aside because of this.<br><br>I don't know who Mors is. &nbsp;Has anyone ever seen him in the game?<br><br>He isn't posting with the intent to debate an opinion. &nbsp;He's posting with the intent to hurt people just because he knows many of us on these boards have either lost someone or are still waiting to hear if our friends and family are safe. &nbsp;People post flames meant to hurt others on these boards all the time, but there is a difference between calling someone a crackwhore as an insult and laughing about real life mass carnage and death. &nbsp;There is a way to do things, and I know I'm not alone in saying that his way of talking about the situation is not welcome here.<br><br>To be honest, the idea of population control that he posted with a <b>=)</b> emoticon had passed through my mind before he said anything. &nbsp;I didn't bring it up because I didn't find it funny when I thought about it. &nbsp;When he mentioned it with a smile, that just told me that he should've been on one of those planes instead of one of the children riding home.<br><br>Sihl<br>Founding Member of Infernos' Hand <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ughie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ghie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 133<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/12/01 12:19:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=140.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ogmuk, please ban Mors...</span><hr size=1> He should be banned simply for posting anonymously. Count his posts. see when his account was created. He is an adolescent troll who should be ignored. He is only posting to cause arguement. In reality he is some adolescent who can't even grasp how he really feels about what is happening in the world around him. His reaction to this is to scream for attention. Ignore him.<br><br>But he is breaking the first and foremost rule on the board. He is posting anonymously using an account he created just to troll.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uraedwulf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raedwulf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 262<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/12/01 12:26:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=140.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ogmuk, please ban Mors...</span><hr size=1> Kani:  I don't see why you're so intent on permitting this little troll to do what he did.  I'm not &quot;hurt&quot; by his comments, but I am offended.  I don't think he ought to be permitted to do so around here.  I'm offended by plenty of other things that happen around here, but this kind of foolishness (especially as it breaks the forum rules) is not something that ought to be put up with. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uiceweaselx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ice Weasel X</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 154<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/12/01 12:33:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=140.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ogmuk, please ban Mors...</span><hr size=1> This message board has rules. &nbsp;Despite the old clich&#0233;, rules are <i>not</i> there just to be broken. &nbsp;The guidelines set forth are there to keep this place a relatively welcome place for the Erollisi Marr community to post. &nbsp;Ogmuk has laid out the rules so people know there are possibilities for banning, and I've made a request because I feel it's warranted.<br><br>His "blips" as you call them have the potential to make people very physically ill. &nbsp;The loss of human life and the amount of hatred being thrown around here aren't things to play around with. &nbsp;His comments aren't the typical "rouse the crowd" comments that people throw around just to start flamewars. &nbsp;People are dead. &nbsp;Many are fearing nuclear consequences. &nbsp;Joking about how this is a good thing due to "population control" or "more available jobs" is in such bad taste that I'd rather see Jevert and Inviticus running around blabbing. &nbsp;This situation doesn't just affect people in New York City; Washington, D.C.; or the other sites of crashes. &nbsp;This is nationwide, and this is worldwide. &nbsp;My friends and family in different countries are both in mourning over people they know and also anxious about what's to come. &nbsp;Multiple countries have closed down air travel and are checking their own defense statuses. &nbsp;That is how serious it is.<br><br>His posts aren't "hurting" me, but they do disgust me, much the same way as someone jumping on live television with a freshly-dug up corpse and ripping pieces of its flesh out with his teeth would. &nbsp;Yeah, most of us live in a "free world." &nbsp;There is a thing called decency though, and it's one of the buttresses of that free world. &nbsp;I feel that I'm an active contributor to this message board community. &nbsp;I don't think that I should be the one to go away just because he wants to come and parade in front of us with his "hee hee look at all the death and carnage" attitude. &nbsp;Read other people's posts and you'll see they all feel the same way. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usalenie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Salenie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/12/01 12:59:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=140.topic&index=11>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ogmuk, please ban Mors...</span><hr size=1> I do, Kanibal.  You are expressing the argument a LOT of people were making when EQ Traders Corner editted Scoppie's post to remove her .sig file.  Don't know if the same people calling for the boycott of that site are the same people calling for the banning of Mors...not quite THAT cynical enough to look up the older thread. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I'll just think 'what goes around comes around'.<br><br>(IMHO--Mors is a kid who wants attention and the best way of handling him is to ignore him.) <p>Salenie Silkweaver<BR>Proud Member of <a href=" http://www.clanbattleaxe.com">Clan Battle Axe</a> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ucaladdor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caladdor</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://wwp.icq.com/scripts/online.dll?icq=9311062&img=5" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 517<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/12/01 1:03:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=140.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ogmuk, please ban Mors...</span><hr size=1> If he signed with his ingame name or real life name/adress/email he would be a fucking sad individual, but by posting anonomously he's nothing other than a troll with very bad taste<br><br>If he would back his posts up by letting people know who he was i could see the case you're arguing Kani ... but not when he's too cowardly to show who he is. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uiceweaselx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ice Weasel X</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 155<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/12/01 1:08:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=140.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ogmuk, please ban Mors...</span><hr size=1> It doesn't matter how strongly we feel about our own opinions. &nbsp;We'd rather not need something horrible or disgusting to be the only means of bringing us together under beliefs or causes. &nbsp;There's another thing that goes hand-in-hand with freedom. &nbsp;That's <i>peace</i>. &nbsp;Sure, blood was shed for that freedom, and more will be shed to keep it. &nbsp;To be truly free though, we have to be <i>safe</i> and free... <i>happy</i> and free.<br><br>There's something else you keep forgetting though. &nbsp;This particular board is Ogmuk's territory. &nbsp;It may belong to ezboard, but he's administering it. &nbsp;It's something of a benevolent dictatorship, not a democracy. &nbsp;In most cases, his word is final. &nbsp;However, I guarantee you that if someone comes here and starts preaching about attacking America (in a serious manner, not like our Canadian neighbors always talk), that the person will be chased off the boards. &nbsp;It's not a <i>right</i> to post here, it's a <i>priviledge</i> granted by ezboard, Ogmuk, and the Erollisi Marr community.<br><br>You're trying to say that buttnuggets like him are making us stronger, and that we're trying to squash his right of free speech. &nbsp;There are limits to that right of free speech, outlined heavily with the idea of common decency. &nbsp;"That which doesn't kill me blahblahblah..." &nbsp;I'd rather stay a little weaker if it means I don't have to put up with this crap. &nbsp;I'd prefer not to get anymore jaded than I already am.<br><br>It's really odd that you're defending him so much. &nbsp;He's continuing to play it off like a big joke, which should tell you he's not trying to make people believe "his opinion." &nbsp;He's just being inappropriate and enjoying it.<br><br>This isn't an issue of freedom of speech. &nbsp;It's an issue of decency and compassion. &nbsp;There are dozens of people here on these boards who are seeking moral support from each other. &nbsp;Simply put, that trash <b>does not belong here.</b> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uraedwulf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raedwulf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 264<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/12/01 2:13:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=140.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ogmuk, please ban Mors...</span><hr size=1> But anonymously?  Forget the moronic and offensive nature of what he said, he did it anonymously.  None of the rest of us are doing so.  I'm sorry that you can't seem to see the difference between suppressing an actual opinion and suppressing idiocy that is only intended to incite. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uiceweaselx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ice Weasel X</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 156<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/12/01 2:15:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=140.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ogmuk, please ban Mors...</span><hr size=1> No, I don't think anyone is going to train him. &nbsp;The reason people are bringing his in-game up is because we want the turd gone. &nbsp;He doesn't have the nerve to say stuff like this if people recognized him in the game, because he's fully aware that it's going to hurt some and offend almost everyone.<br><br>That's not speaking your mind. &nbsp;That's being a sick fuck, and you know it. &nbsp;We've already all decided what our opinions were, and we don't need someone with that garbage coming through here to strengthen it. &nbsp;We <i>really</i> don't need someone around who's going to switch to a new name to try and blindside people with emotional stress when they don't expect it (oh look, a thread by someone new... what the fuck?).<br><br>You sit there and watch as a woman at your office has to be sent home screaming in hysterics because her cousin has just been blown up by a plane crashing into <i>his</i> office. &nbsp;Then come here and try to say, "hey, it's just an opinion," when he's smiling about it and throwing more inappropriate comments around in very severe, morose situation that is causing worldwide anguish. &nbsp;He came here with an unknown name so he could hurt people without getting in trouble.<br><br>There is a time to leave people to their own devices, but not like this. &nbsp;You keep bringing free speech into it. &nbsp;I'm going to keep bringing decency and compassion into it.<br><br>Sihl <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utreage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Treage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/12/01 4:46:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=140.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:Ogmuk, please ban Mors...</span><hr size=1> An anonomous poster with a freshly created account made for the specific purpose of kicking people when they are down does not constitute a benefit to this board. This person went out of their way to start a new ez board account just to do this. This was not an expression of a thought or belief, but done purely to see if it could hurt people.<br><br>I don't think anyone cares to read another word from this anonomous poster ever again. I also don't think anyone would shed a single tear to him being gone either. Lets not confuse freedom of speach for malicious intent.<br><br>Treage Shadowbane <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_b