 valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> hmm</span><hr size=1> If he posted with a real name to identify with, then I would respect his opinion. But by making a new name up, he is just showing he isn't confident enough in his own opinion to use his real IG name and is a coward. Therefore he dosen't deserve the access of this board. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utreage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Treage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/12/01 5:43:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=140.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:Hmm</span><hr size=1> I guess the thing that really ticks me off is the anonimity of the poster. I have read many opinions that I absolutely didn't agree with on this board, but they were from people that I could tie a name and toon with. <br><br>I have even decided not to group with some of the posters here because of their opinions in the past, but I was atleast informed of who it was.<br><br>I may not like what people say, but I can atleast respect them when they don't act as cowardly as the terrorists did in NY.<br><br>I agree with freedom of speach on these boards, but I DO NOT agree with anyone who backs up what this POS has said, or may say in the future. Until he/she/it decides to come forward then my opinion will not change no matter what reasoning is presented.<br><br>Treage Shadowbane <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uumbrae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Umbrae</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.newcreations.net/3d/cubebullet/bulletb_ss1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/12/01 8:48:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=140.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:Hmm</span><hr size=1> I must agree, how ever annoying how ever rude Mors is, he is still entitled to his opinion.  There are a lot of great thing that have happened in this nation when people voiced an opinion that was not accepted by society at large. The end of the Vietnam conflict was in part to such an act. Yet on another note I must say that his total lack of a spine does rather irk me.  so at this point might I ask for a refinement of the rules for this board.<br><br><br>Any post that is made anonymously may the posters IP address added o be used as identification for said individual<br><br>Just an idea <p>My specialties include boiling mobs from the inside out, causing sever amounts of pain for long periods of time, killing things that should kick my arse, Reanimating the dead to do my bidding, Leeching the abilities of my victims and making home baked cookies.  Personally I recommend you try the cookies.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uiceweaselx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ice Weasel X</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 157<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/12/01 9:21:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=140.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:Hmm</span><hr size=1> The thing is, he isn't saying things to state an opinion. &nbsp;He's doing it increase the grief felt by people who have either lost friends or family, or people who just happen to be compassionate enough to feel for those who have. &nbsp;Slayne followed Mors's recent links in his ezboard profile to a UO message board. &nbsp;He did the same thing there, and it was done in the spirit of malice.<br><br>Slayne, if you see this, could you please check your browser history if it's intact and find the URLs of those messages? &nbsp;I'd like to have a little evidence for the people who say he's just stating an opinion instead of deliberately trying to cause pain for fun by taking cheap shots at the grieving masses.<br><br><a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showMessageRange?topicID=2376.topic&start=41&stop=41">Slayne</a> to <a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showMessageRange?topicID=2376.topic&start=49&stop=49">Mors</a> to <a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showMessageRange?topicID=2376.topic&start=52&stop=52">Slayne</a><br><br>You who say he's entitled to say these things as an opinion, do you really think he's just opining about things? &nbsp;Sheesh, when he called it "population control," he said it with a smile. &nbsp;Would you also say that the people who post on the survivor lists with names like Big Gay Al and add comments like, "I know where to get a 10 dollar steak for 5 buck," are entitled to post there because the forms are available to the public?<br><br>Look where he posts. &nbsp;He has only bothered to post on the Rants and Flames section of this message board, because that's the sort of thread he wants. &nbsp;Yeah, I may have been suckered into adding to this, but supporting his "right to post" seems even stupider than trying to get rid of this trash. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uulujainebonelphette.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ulujain Ebonelphette</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_cyanspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 212<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/12/01 9:27:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=140.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:Hmm</span><hr size=1> When you say he posted anon, let me ask, what would you do if he didn't; and no longer played EQ? I.e, he posted under a player name that's no longer active in EQ, like me.<br>What could possibily be your recourse?<br><br>I see words here along the lines of let's hunt him down and get him. Frankly, that appals me. If you knew his RL home address, would you really go after him like that?<br><br>Call me a fucker, but in reading crap like that (which is by no means unique to this board) I'm glad Texas has a concealed gun law.<br><br>Ogmuk probably knows the futility of banning him. Why? In the US at least, it isn't hard to get free ISP accounts and it isn't hard to post from a public place, such as a college or a library...hell, even a workplace.<br><br><br>But writing that you're gonna chase his ass down for a untasteful flip comment is vindictiveness to the power of ten. <p>Admin of Horrorshow Forever, free-falling flamefest board!<BR><font color="red"><a href="http://pub66.ezboard.com/bhorrorshowforever">Horrorshow Forever</a></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uiceweaselx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ice Weasel X</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 158<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/12/01 9:52:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=140.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:Hmm</span><hr size=1> What's disturbing is that he might not even play EverQuest. &nbsp;He could be someone just searching message boards for people to mess with, so no, an ingame name isn't necessarily going to be the answer that some feel it would be.<br><br>The physical threats are crass, but that just proves the kind of situation we're in - the anger, grief, and confusion has people wound tightly enough to resort to that kind of threat more quickly than they probably would have a week ago. &nbsp;I don't agree with the method, but then again I'm 90% pacifist.<br><br>Yes, it's simple to get around an IP banning, but it's even simpler to add addresses and ranges to the blocked list. &nbsp;If someone's at school or at work, banning the range will ensure no more <i>direct</i> contact from any computers on that network without an extra step. &nbsp;If someone has to switch ISPs, that's added effort right there.<br><br>Know what? &nbsp;If Ogmuk said he'd keep the guy out of here, but that it would cost me my own access to the board, I'd agree to it. &nbsp;I'd be missing out on something I've been using for almost a year, but I'd feel vindicated in knowing that the heartless fuck wouldn't be posting crap like that around on these boards in full view of people who don't want or need that sick sort of non-humor. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udwarkarn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dwarkarn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.home.net/freemana/Graphics/mcpi1.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 1434<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/12/01 9:58:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=140.topic&index=26>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:Hmm</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE STA